A policeman attached to the judge of the Magistrate Court in Akure, Ondo State, has tested positive for Coronavirus. SaharaReporters gathered that the officer tested positive after having contact with one of the suspects in the murder of Mrs Funke Olakunri, daughter of Pa Reuben Fasoranti. Although the state government was yet to officially announce the incident, an official of the state’s health ministry confirmed the development. He said the police orderly had been isolated immediately after his test came back positive.



